<font color="#FF0000">PARADOX OF ORANGE</font><br>
<tt>Fri Dec  6 21:45:58 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
I lost a friend to Agent Orange, and gained one becasue of it. Like all aspects of my experience with Vietnam, my understanding of Orange is a melancholy paradox, for which I'd give anything to turn back time and erase it from history. Now there are the Gulf War vets and the Gulf War babies, and it feels like we're reliving the same nightmare in a new era. When will it end? Only when we learn to weigh the costs of war against the costs of &quot;victory,&quot; and understand that the price is too great to ever fight again.
